snippet.textDisplay:
So apparently Coke studio took a famous communist poem , Hum Bhi Dekhenge ( We too will see) by Comrade Faiz Ahmed Faiz , which was made as a criticism of Pakistani state and removed the lines - 

"sab taaj uchhāle jā.eñge 
sab taḳht girā.e jā.eñge " 

(The day Crowns will be hurled in air ,
The day thrones will be toppled )

And made it a ode to Pakistani state. 

And this is why I hate when popular media takes up art from Communists. They gentrify it and take everything radical out of it.
Hum Dekhein Ge' was the revolutionary democratic anthem sung by a defiant Iqbal Bano before a stadium full of 50,000 cheering Pakistanis, and a row of angry army generals which this song openly taunts.
